-- Toronto-Dominion Chief Tells Globe Government Must Tighten Mortgage Rules
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-12-16T09:49:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-16/td-bank-head-blames-government-for-canada-debt-level-globe-says.html
Ed Clark, Toronto-Dominion Bank’s
chief executive officer, said cutting Canada’s excessive
household debt is a matter for the government rather than
financial institutions and would best be tackled through tighter
rules on home mortgages, the Globe & Mail reported.  In an interview with the newspaper, Clark said no bank
wants to lead the way in imposing stricter borrowing conditions,
for fear that it will lose customers to its rivals.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
